        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 2:32PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 232 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Irwinton to near Danville to near Kathleen, and
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Cochran, Irwinton, Dudley, Toomsboro, Danville, Montrose, Allentown,
Coley Station, Tarversville, Sand Bed, Tuckers Crossroad,
Nicklesville, Magnolia, Royal, District Path, Paulk, Goldsboro,
Chappells Mill, Rebie, and Cary.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
